        <h1>LU welcomes ASLEFs intention to call off industrial action</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        28 February 2006
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        London Underground (LU) has welcomed ASLEF's recommendation that strike action planned for 2 March be called off.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            We will continue to meet with the trade unions to discuss and resolve all issues
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>An LU spokesperson said: "We are pleased that ASLEF are to recommend that this Thursday's planned Tube strike is called off, following constructive talks with London Underground.  </p>
<p>"We have maintained throughout that the best way to resolve all issues is through discussion and consultation.</p>
<p>"We have also held constructive talks with RMT and hope that it will also call off any planned strike action.</p>
<p>"We will continue to meet with the trade unions to discuss and resolve all issues."</p>
<p>LU is continuing talks with the RMT union to avert strike action planned for the same day.</p>
